CHOLERA, DIARRHEA & DYSENTERY UPDATE (19): ASIA (SYRIA)
*******************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 15 May 2018 EEST
Source: Baladi-News [in Arabic, trans. Mod.MM, edited]
https://bit.ly/2IQYGhD


More than 10 fatal cases of cholera have been registered in the IDP [internally displaced persons] camp near Deir ez-Zor rural area according to the local news network "Furat Post".

The cause of the cholera outbreak is possibly related to contaminated water sources in the camp, which receives its water supply from water tankers previously used for other purposes.

The network warned of the spread of infection among a larger number of people if preventive measures are not taken, through awareness campaigns and supply of safe water.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
via
ProMED-MENA
<promed-mena@promedmail.org>

[Given the state of Syria and its civil war, it is not surprising that enteric diseases are an issue. Even with a case fatality rate of 1 percent, that would mean that 1000 cases have occurred. One of the issues that occurs in such situations is that lack of diagnostic tools to confirm that cholera is present. - Mod.LL

